defs.docs:
The `termios` crate provides Rust bindings for the POSIX termios API that is implemented on
 Unix operating systems. The termios API is defined in the [IEEE Std 1003.1 ("POSIX.1")
 specification](http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/basedefs/termios.h.html).

defs.name: tcsetattr
defs.value: fn (fd: c_int, optional_actions: c_int, termios_p: *const ::os::target::termios) -> c_int

defs.name: termios
defs.value: termios { c_iflag, c_oflag, c_cflag, c_lflag, c_cc }

defs.name: from_fd
defs.docs: Creates a `Termios` structure based on the current settings of a file descriptor.

defs.name: cfgetispeed
defs.docs: Gets the input baud rate stored in a `Termios` structure.

defs.name: cfgetospeed
defs.docs: Gets the output baud rate stored in a `Termios` structure.

defs.name: cfsetspeed
defs.docs: Sets input and output baud rates.

defs.name: cfmakeraw
defs.docs: Sets flags to disable all input and output processing.

defs.name: tcdrain
defs.docs: Blocks until all output written to the file descriptor is transmitted.

defs.name: tcflow
defs.docs: Suspends or restarts transmission or reception of data.

defs.name: tcflush
defs.docs: Discards data waiting in the terminal device's buffers.

defs.name: tcgetattr
defs.docs: Populates a `Termios` structure with parameters associated with a terminal.

defs.name: tcsetattr
defs.value: fn (fd: RawFd, action: c_int, termios: &Termios) -> io::Result<()>

defs.name: tcgetsid
defs.docs: Returns the process group ID of the controlling terminal's session.

defs.name: tcsendbreak
defs.docs: Transmits data to generate a break condition.
